The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Motera to host 1st Test vs England 
                                                                                                                                                                                                     CRICKET BRIEFS
                      
	Motera to host 1st Test vs England   
	New Delhi: Ahmedabad will host the first Test between India and England when Michael Vaughans side come to India for a two-Test and seven-ODI series in November-December, the final itinerary of which will be announced soon by the BCCI. The second Test of the series will be played in Mumbai before the two teams lock horns in a one-day series. The first of the seven one-dayers will be played in the capital. Indore, Rajkot, Jamshedpur, Cuttack, Guwahati and Kanpur will host the remaining matches of the series.  
	ECB impressed         
	 Mumbai: England and Wales Cricket Board has been left astonished by the BCCI-promoted Indian Premier Leagues success and is comparing the billion-dollar Twenty20 extravaganza in scope and scale to the Rugby World Cup. Chairman Giles Clarke, who witnessed the initial rounds of the IPL spectacle with his CEO David Collier, told the ECBs AGM at Lords on Tuesday that his admiration for what had been achieved by the Sharad Pawar-headed BCCI was huge. It was, as the Indians say, a great tamasha. There was light, glitz, glamour and music. We must congratulate them (BCCI) on establishing a tournament which has the same scope and scale which can be compared to the Rugby World Cup, Clarke told the members of the ECB, according to a media release.         
	Royal plan         
	 Jaipur: Indian Premier Leagues Jaipur franchise owners, Emerging Media, has launched Rajasthan Royals cricket development program to train young cricketers.         
	Darren Berry, the director of coaching in the Rajasthan Royals, told reporters that the development programme would have Shane Warne to guide the youngsters from time to time. Along with Darren, Jeremy Snape and Harish Joshi will look after the coaching.         
	Eves upbeat         
	 Dubai: The Indian womens cricket team will attempt to win the Asia Cup for an unprecedented fourth time with skipper Mithali Raj and pace spearhead Jhulan Goswami also aiming for individual milestones in the tournament starting Friday in Sri Lanka.         
	The tournament  also featuring Sri Lanka, Pakistan and debutants Bangladesh  will be played till May 11 and India will take on Bangladesh in their lung-opener. Its definitely part of our preparations for the World Cup and is the start of the season for us. Were confident, Mithali said.                                                                                                                            
